# NEXUS CHAT

A real-time chat application built with Node.js, Socket.IO, and vanilla JavaScript.

---

## Features

- **Global Channel** — `#general` room for all connected users
- **Direct Messages** — private one-on-one conversations
- **Typing Indicators** — see when others are typing
- **Message Reactions** — react with emojis (right-click or long-press a message)
- **Read Receipts** — single ✓ (sent) and double ✓✓ (seen)
- **Emoji Picker** — built-in emoji panel
- **Online Presence** — live user list with online/offline status
- **Unread Badges** — unread counts on DMs and general channel
- **Dark / Light Theme** — toggle in the sidebar footer
- **Session Persistence** — username saved across refreshes
- **Mobile Responsive** — slide-out sidebar on small screens

---

## Project Structure

```
ChatApp/
├── index.html    # UI markup & layout
├── style.css     # Styling & CSS variables (dark/light themes)
├── code.js       # Frontend logic (Socket.IO client)
└── server.js     # Backend (Express + Socket.IO server)
```

---

## Prerequisites

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) v16 or higher
- npm (comes with Node.js)

---

## Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone or download the project
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd ChatApp

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install express socket.io
```

---

## Running the App

```bash
node server.js
```

Then open your browser and go to:

```
http://localhost:5001
```

To use a different port, set the `PORT` environment variable:

```bash
PORT=3000 node server.js
```

---

## Usage

1. Open the app in your browser.
2. Enter a username (up to 24 characters) and click **Enter the nexus**.
3. Start chatting in **#general**, or click any user in the sidebar to open a **Direct Message**.
4. Use the 😊 button to open the emoji picker.
5. **Right-click** (or long-press on mobile) a message to add a reaction.
6. Click the sun/moon icon in the sidebar footer to toggle **dark/light theme**.
7. Click the exit icon to log out and clear your session.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer    | Technology                        |
|----------|-----------------------------------|
| Server   | Node.js, Express                  |
| Realtime | Socket.IO                         |
| Frontend | Vanilla JS, HTML5, CSS3           |
| Fonts    | Syne, Instrument Sans, Geist Mono |

---

## Notes

- Chat history is stored **in-memory** (last 100 messages). Data is lost when the server restarts.
- No database or authentication is included — this is a demo/prototype.
- For production use, consider adding MongoDB/Redis for persistence and JWT for auth.